    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix unreachable code path in SLDCH generation due to incorrect conditional logic\n\n### Summary\nThe `generate_sldch` function in the LTE UE transport layer contained an `AssertFatal(false, ...)` that always triggered, causing the program to crash and making any subsequent code unreachable. This issue affected the sidelink transmission chain when SLDCH data was present.\n\nWhen the UE attempted to transmit sidelink data, the `phy_procedures_UE_SL_TX` function would call `generate_sldch`, which immediately failed with a fatal assertion instead of gracefully handling the unimplemented functionality. This caused the entire sidelink transmission chain to halt unexpectedly.\n\nThe problem was also present in similar functions (`generate_slss` and `generate_slsch`) which had the same pattern of always-fatal assertions instead of proper stub implementations.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/LTE_UE_TRANSPORT/sldch.c`: Replaced `AssertFatal(false, ...)` with warning log and TODO comment\n- `openair1/PHY/LTE_UE_TRANSPORT/slss.c`: Replaced `AssertFatal(1==0, ...)` with warning log and TODO comment  \n- `openair1/PHY/LTE_UE_TRANSPORT/slsch.c`: Replaced `AssertFatal(false, ...)` with warning log and TODO comment\n\n"
}